column7: 3_Race_TEXT_What is your race/ethnicity? Select all that apply. - Other (please specify): - Text

column9: 4_Gender_TEXT_What is your gender identity? - Other (please specify): - Text
column10: 5_PoliticalParty_In politics today, do you consider yourself a Republican, a Democrat, an Independent, or something else? - Selected Choice
column11: 5_PoliticalParty_TEXT_In politics today, do you consider yourself a Republican, a Democrat, an Independent, or something else? - Something else (please specify): - Text
column12: 6_Education_What is the highest level of education you have completed or are currently working toward?
column13: 7_PoliticalViews_How would you describe your political views? - Selected Choice
column14: 7_PoliticalViews_TEXT_How would you describe your political views? - Other (please specify): - Text
column15: 8_Religiosity_How often do you attend religious services?
column16: 9_ElectionViews_Which of the following statements most closely describes your views on the 2020 U.S. presidential election?
column17: 10_SepChurch&State_Which of the following statements most closely describes your views on separation of church and state?
column18: 11_AbortionViews_Which of the following statements most closely describes your views on abortion?
column19: 12_DeathPenaltyViews_Which of the following statements most closely describes your views on capital punishment (the death penalty)?
column20: 13_DoctorPenalty_If a doctor performs multiple illegal abortions, which of the following do you think would be the most appropriate penalty?
column21: 14_PatientPenalty_If a woman receives an illegal abortion, which of the following do you think would be the most appropriate penalty?
column22: 15_CourtApproval_Do you approve of the recent U.S. Supreme Court decision to overturn Roe v. Wade?
column23: 16_Approval%_What percentage of Americans do you think approve of the recent Supreme Court decision to overturn Roe v. Wade? Use the slider below to select your estimation.
column24: 17_ExceptFetalDeath_Do you think abortion should be legal in cases where the fetus has a disease that will cause it to die before or shortly after birth?
column25: 18_ExceptRapeIncest_Do you think abortion should be legal in cases of rape or incest?
column26: 19_ExceptMomsLife_Do you think abortion should be legal in cases where the pregnancy threatens the mother's life?
column27: 20_EmbryoisPerson_Do you believe that a fertilized egg (embryo) is a person?
column28: 21_AbortionCasualSex_How much do you agree with this statement?: If abortions are difficult or impossible to get, people will be less likely to have casual sex with multiple partners.
column29: 22_FourTrimesters_Is the following statement true or false?: There are four trimesters in a pregnancy.
column30: 23_StateLawViews_Which of the following statements most accurately describes your views on your state's abortion laws?
column31: 24_StateRestrict_At what stage of pregnancy is abortion currently restricted in your state?
column32: 25_StateExceptFetus_Does your state's current law(s) allow for abortion in cases where the fetus has a disease that will cause it to die before or shortly after birth?
column33: 26_StateExceptRape_Does your state's current law(s) allow for abortion in cases of rape or incest?
column34: 27_StateExceptMom_Does your state's current law(s) allow for abortion in cases where the pregnancy threatens the mother's life?
column35: 28_Condoms%_For women who use condoms as their birth control method, what percent will become pregnant by accident within one year? Use the slider below to make your guess.
column36: 29_Pill%_For women who use birth control pills as their birth control method, what percent will become pregnant by accident within one year? Use the slider below to make your guess.
column37: 30_PullingOut%_For women who use the "pulling out" method as their birth control method, what percent will become pregnant by accident within one year? Use the slider below to make your guess.
column38: 31_ImplantFail%_About what percent of the time does a fertilized egg (embryo) fail to implant in the uterus (womb) and grow into a fetus? Use the slider below to make your guess.
column39: 32_OutsideImplant%_About what percent of the time does a fertilized egg (embryo) implant outside of the uterus (womb)? Use the slider below to make your guess.
column40: 33_Miscarriage%_About what percent of pregnancies end in miscarriage?  Use the slider below to make your guess.
column41: 34_EctopicSurvive_Is the following statement true or false?: An embryo that implants outside the womb (an "ectopic pregnancy") can survive to be born.
column42: 35_EctopicSurgery_Is the following statement true or false?: An embryo that implants outside the womb (an "ectopic pregnancy") can be surgically re-implanted in the womb.
column43: 36_AssaultResponse_Is the following statement true or false?: When a woman is sexually assaulted, her body naturally takes steps to prevent pregnancy in response to the assault.
column44: 37_FetalWeight_On average, how much does a typical fetus weigh at the end of the first trimester of pregnancy?
column45: 38_FetalLength_On average, about how long is a typical fetus at the end of the first trimester of pregnancy?
column50: 43_SelectIUD_Which of the following images shows an IUD (intrauterine device)? Select all that apply.
column51: 44_AgeofConsent_What do you think the legal age of consent should be for engaging in sexual activity?
column52: 45_CasualSex_How much do you agree with this statement?: Casual sex, or sexual promiscuity, is a major cause of societal problems.
column53: 46_WomanCasualSex_How much do you agree with this statement?: There is nothing wrong with a woman who engages in casual sex with multiple partners.
column54: 47_EmbryosLab_How much do you agree with this statement?: Fertilized eggs (embryos) should not be created in a lab for the use of in-vitro fertilization if not all of the embryos will eventually be implanted.
column55: 48_AbortionTrans_Do you think abortion should be legal in the following situation?: A genetic test of the fetus is able to detect that the baby will grow up to be transgender.
column56: 49_OtherThoughts_If you'd like to share additional thoughts on any of the topics mentioned in this survey, please do so in the box below.

column56: I think that abortion should be a woman's right. No one knows the circumstances of what the woman is going through. She could have been raped, the child could have defects, she could be too young to have a child. Yes, there is adoption for a mother to give her healthy baby up, but it's a mother's choice. Not every mother is thinking straight when she becomes pregnant. I would hope that every pregnant mom would have someone to talk to first before making that decision, but ultimately it is her body. My daughter got pregnant at 16 and she couldn't afford to keep her baby, so she allowed us to adopt her child. We are very fortunate to have been able to do this, but not everyone can. We also told our daughter we would do this only once. We adopted her at the age of 5 when we were in our 40's. When we adopted our granddaughter, we were in our late 50's. She is 8 years old, and we are 63 and 67. Our daughter since then has had 2 abortions, we just couldn't possibly raise 2 other children. The courts told her the same thing; we couldn't adopt anymore children. I wish she would use birth control, but she won't.
